'''''Testimony''''' is the [[studio album|debut album]] by American recording artist [[August Alsina]]. The album was released on April 15, 2014 by [[Def Jam Recordings]]. The album was supported by five official singles; "[[I Luv This Shit]]" featuring [[Trinidad James]], "Ghetto," "[[Numb (August Alsina song)|Numb]]" featuring [[B.o.B]] and [[Yo Gotti]], "Make It Home" featuring [[Young Jeezy|Jeezy]], and "Kissin' on My Tattoos," along with the [[promotional single]] "Benediction" featuring [[Rick Ross]]. Upon its release, ''Testimony'' was met with generally positive reviews from [[music critics]].

==Promotion==

===Singles===
On February 14, 2013, the music video was released for "[[I Luv This Shit]]" featuring [[Trinidad James]].<ref>{{cite web|title=I Luv This Shit (Explicit) - August Alsina|url=http://www.vevo.com/watch/august-alsina/i-luv-this-shit-explicit/USUV71300194|work=[[Vevo]]|publisher=|accessdate=February 14, 2013}}</ref> Five days later, "I Luv This Shit" was released for digital download.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-luv-this-sh*t-feat.-trinidad/id601147368 |title=iTunes - Music - I Luv This Sh*t (feat. Trinidad James) - Single by August Alsina |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2013-02-19 |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> The song peaked at number 48 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and number 13 on the [[Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1562258/August+Alsina/chart?f=379 |title=August Alsina - Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1562258/August+Alsina/chart?f=367 |title=August Alsina - Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> On December 9, 2013, the second single from the album, "Ghetto" featuring [[Rich Homie Quan]] was serviced to [[urban contemporary]] radio in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frequencynews.com/flippagefreq/flip-freq-dec-2013/index.html#p=18 |title=freq-flip-dec-2013 |publisher=Frequencynews.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2013/12/august-alsina-ft-yo-gotti-ghetto |title=August Alsina f/ Yo Gotti "Ghetto" |publisher=Complex |date=2013-12-18 |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> It was later released for digital download on February 11, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Alsina_Ghetto?id=Bfi2er5grpq524w24knlj6b3bdq |title=August Alsina: Ghetto - Muziek op Google Play |publisher=Play.google.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref>

On December 2, 2013, the music video was released for "[[Numb (August Alsina song)|Numb]]" featuring [[B.o.B.]] and Yo Gotti.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/new-video-august-alsina-feat-yo-gotti-bob-numb |title=New Video: August Alsina Feat. Yo Gotti & B.o.B. 'Numb' |publisher=Vibe |date=2013-12-02 |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> Then on December 10, 2013, the album's third single "Numb" was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.com/Numb-feat-B-o-B-Clean/dp/B00GWYXXRU/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1397928549&sr=8-1&keywords=august+alsina+numb |title=Numb [feat. B.o.B&#93; [Clean&#93;: August Alsina: MP3 Downloads |publisher=Amazon.com |date=2013-12-10 |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> On January 15, 2014, the album's fourth single "Make It Home" featuring [[Young Jeezy|Jeezy]] was released for download.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.com/Make-Home-feat-Jeezy-Explicit/dp/B00HVQFECA/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1397928885&sr=8-1&keywords=august+alsina+make+it+home |title=Make It Home [feat. Jeezy&#93; [Explicit&#93;: August Alsina: MP3 Downloads |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> It was sent to US urban contemporary radio on March 3, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases |title=Urban/UAC Future Releases |publisher=All Access Music Group |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Nh1eZYsB |archivedate=2014-02-27}}</ref> On February 13, 2014, the music video was released for "Make It Home".<ref>{{cite web|author=Miranda J. |url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2014/02/music-august-alsina/ |title=Music Saves August Alsina's Life In "Make It Home" Video - XXL |publisher=Xxlmag.com |date=2014-02-13 |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref>

On April 1, 2014, the album's fifth single "Kissin' On My Tattoos" was released.<ref name="amazon1">{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.com/Kissin-On-My-Tattoos-Clean/dp/B00JE45TBI/ref=dm_att_trk6 |title=Kissin' On My Tattoos [Clean&#93;: August Alsina: MP3 Downloads |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-19}}</ref> On April 15, 2014, the music video was released for "Get Ya Money" featuring [[Fabolous]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/04/15/video-august-alsina-f-fabolous-get-ya-money/ |title=Video: August Alsina f/ Fabolous <U+2013> <U+2018>Get Ya Money<U+2019> |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date=2014-04-15 |accessdate=2014-07-31}}</ref> On June 26, 2014, the music video was released for "FML" featuring [[Pusha T]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/06/26/video-august-alsina-f-pusha-t-fml/ |title=Video: August Alsina f/ Pusha T <U+2013> <U+2018>FML<U+2019> |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date=2014-06-26 |accessdate=2014-07-31}}</ref> The album's sixth official single "No Love", was serviced to [[urban adult contemporary]] radio in the United States on July 29, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|title=Future Releases|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ROodUrv6|archivedate=2014-07-28}}</ref> On July 1, 2014, the music video was released for "Benediction" featuring [[Rick Ross]], the video also features appearances from [[DJ Khaled]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/06/30/video-august-alsina-f-rick-ross-benediction/ |title=Video: August Alsina f/ Rick Ross <U+2013> <U+2018>Benediction<U+2019> |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date=2014-06-30 |accessdate=2014-07-31}}</ref>

===Tour===
August Alsina will begin the Testimony Live tour in the United States on August 14, 2014.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/06/24/august-alsina-announces-testimony-live-tour/ |title=August Alsina Announced 'Testimony Live' Tour |work=[[Rap-Up]] |date=2014-06-24 |accessdate=2014-06-25}}</ref>

